modules.description: This module provides a function `of_fd` that maps a Unix file descriptor into a `Cstruct.t` buffer, allowing direct access to file contents in memory. It works with Unix file descriptors and the `Cstruct.t` data type, which represents structured binary data. A concrete use case is efficiently reading and manipulating file contents without intermediate copying, such as parsing binary file formats or memory-mapped I/O operations.
